## ğŸš€ Complete Setup Guide

### Step 1: Clone the Repository
```bash
# Clone the project
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/exampro.git

# Navigate to project directory
cd exampro
```

### Step 2: Database Configuration

#### 2.1 Start MySQL Server
```bash
# Windows
net start MySQL80

# macOS
brew services start mysql

# Linux
sudo systemctl start mysql
```

#### 2.2 Create Database
```bash
# Login to MySQL (enter your root password when prompted)
mysql -u root -p

# Create database
CREATE DATABASE test_platform_db;

# Verify database creation
SHOW DATABASES;

# Exit MySQL
exit;
```

### Step 3: Gmail SMTP Setup (For Email Verification)

#### 3.1 Enable 2-Step Verification

1. Go to: https://myaccount.google.com/security
2. Scroll to "Signing in to Google"
3. Click "2-Step Verification"
4. Follow the setup process

#### 3.2 Generate App Password

1. Go to: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
2. In "Select app" dropdown â†’ Choose "Mail"
3. In "Select device" dropdown â†’ Choose "Other (Custom name)"
4. Enter name: `ExamPro`
5. Click "Generate"
6. Copy the 16-character password (format: `abcd efgh ijkl mnop`)
7. **Important:** Save this password - you won't see it again!

### Step 4: Configure Application Properties

Navigate to: `backend/src/main/resources/application.properties`

**Update these values:**
```properties
# ================= DATABASE =================
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/test_platform_db?useSSL=false&serverTimezone=UTC
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=YOUR_MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD

# ================= JPA / HIBERNATE =================
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.dialect=org.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect

# ================= EMAIL (GMAIL SMTP) =================
spring.mail.host=smtp.gmail.com
spring.mail.port=587
spring.mail.username=your.email@gmail.com
spring.mail.password=abcdefghijklmnop

spring.mail.properties.mail.smtp.auth=true
spring.mail.properties.mail.smtp.starttls.enable=true
```

**Replace:**
- `YOUR_MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD` â†’ Your MySQL root password
- `your.email@gmail.com` â†’ Your Gmail address
- `abcdefghijklmnop` â†’ Your 16-char app password (remove spaces)

### Step 5: Build and Run Backend
```bash
# Navigate to backend folder
cd backend

# Clean and build project
mvn clean install

# Run Spring Boot application
mvn spring-boot:run
```

**âœ… Success indicators:**
```
Started BackendApplication in X.XXX seconds (JVM running for X.XXX)
Tomcat started on port(s): 8080 (http) with context path ''
```

**If you see this, backend is running successfully! âœ…**

### Step 6: Run Frontend

Choose one of these methods:

#### Option A: Live Server (Recommended for Development)

1. Install **Live Server** extension in VS Code
2. Open `frontend/index.html` in VS Code
3. Right-click â†’ Select "Open with Live Server"
4. Frontend will run on: `http://localhost:5500`

#### Option B: Python HTTP Server
```bash
# Navigate to frontend folder
cd frontend

# Start server (Python 3)
python -m http.server 5500

# OR Python 2
python -m SimpleHTTPServer 5500
```

Frontend will run on: `http://localhost:5500`

#### Option C: Direct File Access

1. Navigate to `frontend` folder
2. Double-click `index.html`
3. Opens in default browser

**âš ï¸ Note:** Some features may not work due to CORS restrictions with this method.

