## ğŸ”Œ API Documentation

### Base URL
```
http://localhost:8080/api
```

### ğŸ” Authentication Endpoints

#### 1. Register User
```http
POST /auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

Response: "VERIFICATION_SENT" | "EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS" | "WEAK_PASSWORD"
```

#### 2. Verify Email OTP
```http
POST /auth/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "code": "123456"
}

Response: "VERIFIED" | "INVALID_CODE" | "USER_NOT_FOUND"
```

#### 3. Login
```http
POST /auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

Response: "LOGIN_SUCCESS" | "USER_NOT_FOUND" | "INVALID_PASSWORD" | "EMAIL_NOT_VERIFIED"
```

---

### ğŸ“ Test Management Endpoints

#### 4. Create Test
```http
POST /tests/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Math Quiz",
  "duration": 30,
  "description": "Chapter 1 Test",
  "date": "2026-02-10",
  "time": "14:00",
  "createdBy": "john@example.com",
  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "What is 2+2?",
      "options": ["3", "4", "5", "6"],
      "correctAnswer": 1
    }
  ]
}

Response:
{
  "status": "SUCCESS",
  "testCode": "ABC12XYZ",
  "testId": 1,
  "message": "Test created successfully"
}
```

#### 5. Get Test by Code (for taking)
```http
GET /tests/take/{testCode}?email={studentEmail}

Example: GET /tests/take/ABC12XYZ?email=alice@example.com

Response:
{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Math Quiz",
  "duration": 30,
  "totalQuestions": 5,
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "questionText": "What is 2+2?",
      "optionA": "3",
      "optionB": "4",
      "optionC": "5",
      "optionD": "6"
      // Note: correctAnswer NOT included
    }
  ]
}
```

#### 6. Check if Already Taken
```http
GET /tests/check-attempt/{testCode}?email={studentEmail}

Example: GET /tests/check-attempt/ABC12XYZ?email=alice@example.com

Response:
{
  "alreadyTaken": true,
  "score": 8,
  "totalQuestions": 10,
  "submittedAt": "2026-02-06T14:30:00"
}
```

#### 7. Submit Test
```http
POST /tests/submit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "testCode": "ABC12XYZ",
  "studentEmail": "alice@example.com",
  "studentName": "Alice Smith",
  "answers": {
    "1": 1,    // Question ID 1 â†’ Selected B (index 1)
    "2": 2,    // Question ID 2 â†’ Selected C (index 2)
    "3": 0     // Question ID 3 â†’ Selected A (index 0)
  }
}

Response:
{
  "score": 8,
  "totalQuestions": 10,
  "percentage": 80.0,
  "correctAnswers": {
    "1": 1,
    "2": 3,
    "3": 0
  },
  "studentAnswers": {
    "1": 1,
    "2": 2,
    "3": 0
  }
}
```

#### 8. Get My Created Tests
```http
GET /tests/my-tests?email={creatorEmail}

Example: GET /tests/my-tests?email=john@example.com

Response: [
  {
    "id": 1,
    "title": "Math Quiz",
    "testCode": "ABC12XYZ",
    "duration": 30,
    "createdAt": "2026-02-06T10:00:00",
    "status": "active"
  }
]
```

